plan funded status
due to an increase in the present value of
pension obligations, a number of the companys pension
plans were underfunded at october1, 2005, having
accumulated benefit obligations exceeding the fair value of plan
assets. for these plans, the fair value of plan assets
aggregated $3.4billion, the accumulated benefit
obligations aggregated $4.5billion and the projected
benefit obligations aggregated $4.9billion. as a result,
the company has recorded an additional minimum pension liability
adjustment of $1.1billion as of october1, 2005. the
additional minimum pension liability adjustment at
september30, 2004 was $415million. the increase in
the additional minimum pension liability adjustment of
$709million in the current year was primarily due to a
decrease in the discount rate from 6.30% at september30,
2004 to 5.25% at october1, 2005. this increase resulted in
an after-tax adjustment of $448million that was recorded
as a decrease of shareholders equity through accumulated
other comprehensive income in fiscal 2005.
the companys total accumulated pension
benefit obligations at october1, 2005 and
september30, 2004 were $4.6billion and
$3.5billion, respectively, of which 97.3% and 95.2%,
respectively, were vested.
the accumulated postretirement medical benefit
obligations and fair value of plan assets for postretirement
medical plans with accumulated postretirement medical benefit
obligations in excess of plan assets were $1.2billion and
$260million, respectively, at year end 2005 and
$954million and $215million, respectively at year
end 2004.
